<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,942,1147]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,258,1050,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remark:</emphasis>
This is a subcosmopolitan, often horticultural pest species of East Mediterranean origin. The first record was said to have been checked by J.G. Blower, a renowned British specialist. The second Indian record under the name of one of the junior synonyms, 
<taxonomicName box="[569,717,1122,1147]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Iulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis box="[569,717,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">N. pulchellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is likely to be a misidentification.
</paragraph>
